<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12021f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12021f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12021f"> 21(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Helena &amp; Montgomery</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">C&apos;&eacute;tait dans cette solitude myst&eacute;rieuse que <mark>Montgommery et la belle H&eacute;l&egrave;ne</mark> de Terregatte cachaient, habituellement, leurs tendres et fid&egrave;les amours. Depuis des mois, avant l&apos;aurore, ils se retrouvaient, chaque jour, sur le Mont-B&eacute;l&eacute;nus. Dans la paix nocturne, isol&eacute;s du reste du monde, ils &eacute;changeaient leurs r&ecirc;ves, leurs caresses, et leurs baisers et bient&ocirc;t, ce fut pour eux un charme p&eacute;n&eacute;trant que d&apos;&ecirc;tre ainsi oblig&eacute;s de dissimuler leur mutuelle tendresse, puisque le p&egrave;re d&apos;H&eacute;l&egrave;ne ne voulait point que celle-ci &eacute;pous&acirc;t un chevalier brave et loyal, sans doute, entre tous, mais dont la famille &eacute;tait sa rivale par la gloire et par la fortune depuis pr&egrave;s de quatre si&egrave;cles! <font color="green">[At half a mile from Mont-Belenus, its brother of granite, the Mont-Saint-Michel appears, large and regular, dominating the lands of the south that lead to Dol in a circus that is veiled by the distant mist. <br>It was in this mysterious solitude that Montgommery and the beautiful H&eacute;l&egrave;ne of Terregatte used to hide their tender and faithful love. For months, before sunrise, they would meet, each day, on the Mont-Belenus. In the nocturnal quiet, isolated from the rest of the world, they exchanged dreams, caresses, kisses and soon, it was for them deeply entrancing to be thus obliged to hide their mutual tenderness, because the father of H&eacute;l&egrave;ne did not want her to marry the knight, no doubt brave and loyal above all, but whose family had been his rival in glory and fortune for close to four centuries.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 34</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
